The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Thursday, August 12, 2004 				 Subhas aye opens pumps
 A STAFF REPORTER																								The 40-hour petroleum strike, that saw over 2,200 pumps across the state down shutters, was called off on Wednesday evening after transport minister Subhas Chakraborty held an hour-long meeting with the fuel dealers .																								He has promised them in writing that their major demands would be looked into.																								The pump-owners want an end to the frequent hike in oil prices, a change in the mode of commission, paring of sales tax, abolition of cess and a check on robberies at pumps.																								The minister will urge the petroleum ministry to ensure transparency in market dealings and a check on oil price upheavals.
